<td box="[1373,1706,1232,1280]" gridcol="4" gridrow="9" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Campanulate, not constricted upward</td>
<td box="[1727,2051,1232,1280]" gridcol="5" gridrow="9" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Urceolate,</td>
</tr>
<tr box="[144,2051,1316,1365]" gridrow="10" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">
<th box="[144,283,1316,1365]" gridcol="0" gridrow="10" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Flowers color</th>
<td box="[306,642,1316,1365]" gridcol="1" gridrow="10" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Pink–purple, pink–lavender, to yellowish with lilac, or creamy–white</td>
<td box="[658,1000,1316,1365]" gridcol="2" gridrow="10" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Pale purple, ochroleucous (when dry)</td>
<td box="[1016,1350,1316,1365]" gridcol="3" gridrow="10" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Purple to pink–purple</td>
<td box="[1373,1706,1316,1365]" gridcol="4" gridrow="10" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Pink, pink–purple</td>
<td box="[1727,2051,1316,1365]" gridcol="5" gridrow="10" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Petals blue to blue–violet and basally white</td>
</tr>
<tr box="[144,2051,1398,1417]" gridrow="11" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">
<th box="[144,283,1398,1417]" gridcol="0" gridrow="11" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Banner size</th>
<td box="[306,642,1398,1417]" gridcol="1" gridrow="11" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">12–24.5 mm long</td>
<td box="[658,1000,1398,1417]" gridcol="2" gridrow="11" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">7.2–10 mm long</td>
<td box="[1016,1350,1398,1417]" gridcol="3" gridrow="11" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">13–17 mm long</td>
<td box="[1373,1706,1398,1417]" gridcol="4" gridrow="11" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">13.2–18 mm long</td>
<td box="[1727,2051,1398,1417]" gridcol="5" gridrow="11" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">14–16 mm long</td>
</tr>
<tr box="[144,2051,1455,1680]" gridrow="12" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">
<th box="[144,283,1455,1680]" gridcol="0" gridrow="12" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Pods</th>
<td box="[306,642,1455,1680]" gridcol="1" gridrow="12" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Humistrate, ovate, elliptic, lunate to linear–oblong, 9-25 mm long, inflated but never bladdery, contracted distally into a short beak, valves, stiffly papery, leathery to subligneous, with a complete septum. Not concealed by the calyx</td>
<td box="[658,1000,1455,1680]" gridcol="2" gridrow="12" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Spreading ascending to declined, sessile to short stipitate (2–3 mm), 10-18 mm long, strongly compressed triquetrous, oblong, valves papery, with a complete septum. Not concealed by the calyx</td>
<td box="[1016,1350,1455,1680]" gridcol="3" gridrow="12" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Erect, sessile or with stipe-like up to 1 mm long, 12-24 mm long, obliquely ovoid to ellipsoid, turgid to inflated, deltoid or acuminate distally, 1.2–2.4 cm long, slightly compressed, valves stiffly papery or leathery black or white–strigulose with a complete septum. Not concealed by the calyx</td>
<td box="[1373,1706,1455,1680]" gridcol="4" gridrow="12" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">pod narrowly to broadly ovate– acumminate or oblong, slightly or greatly inflated, 12–22 mm long, incurved, contracted distally into a triangular beak, valves papery, glabrous or minute pubescent, with a complete septum. Not concealed by the calyx</td>
<td box="[1727,2051,1455,1680]" gridcol="5" gridrow="12" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Elliptic to suboblong, tumescent, leathery slightly compressed laterally, abruptly contracted at the apex, 6–8 mm long. Complete septum. Concealed by the calyx</td>
</tr>
<tr box="[144,2051,1721,1740]" gridrow="13" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">
<th box="[144,283,1721,1740]" gridcol="0" gridrow="13" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Ovules</th>
<td box="[306,642,1721,1740]" gridcol="1" gridrow="13" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">20–31</td>
<td box="[658,1000,1721,1740]" gridcol="2" gridrow="13" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">9–18</td>
<td box="[1016,1350,1721,1740]" gridcol="3" gridrow="13" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">20–30</td>
<td box="[1373,1706,1721,1740]" gridcol="4" gridrow="13" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">18–22</td>
<td box="[1727,2051,1721,1740]" gridcol="5" gridrow="13" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">4</td>
</tr>
</table>
</paragraph>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="83" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1451,158,292]" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,356,158,184]" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Etymology:—</emphasis>
The name 
<taxonomicName box="[469,561,159,184]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Astragalus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rupertii">
<emphasis box="[469,561,159,184]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Rupertii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of this new section is in honor to Rupert Charles Barneby (1911–2000), specialist and author of the monumental work of 
<taxonomicName box="[575,696,194,220]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Astragalus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[575,696,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Astragalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of North America.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1451,158,292]" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">
The next dichotomous key is added to recognize and differentiate this new section from the other ones that grouped species in 
<collectingCountry box="[351,437,266,292]" name="Mexico" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Mexico</collectingCountry>
(adapted from 
<bibRefCitation author="Barneby, R. C." box="[609,770,266,292]" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" pagination="1 - 1188" refId="ref5365" refString="Barneby, R. C. (1964) Atlas of North American Astragalus. Memoirs of the New York Botanical Garden 13: 1 - 1188." type="journal article" year="1964">Barneby 1964</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Estrada, C. E. &amp; Villarreal, Q. J. &amp; Encina, D. J." box="[781,996,266,292]" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" pagination="163 - 172" refId="ref5624" refString="Estrada, C. E., Villarreal, Q. J. &amp; Encina, D. J. (2020) A new species and a new section of Astragalus (Fabaceae: Papilionoideae) from Mexico. Phytotaxa 428 (3): 163 - 172. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 428.3.1" type="journal article" year="2020">
Estrada 
<emphasis box="[872,928,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
